    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but if it's just a neutral tool, why does it seem like it's so often used to roll back rights that people have relied on for decades? wouldn't a more \"living\" approach be better for keeping the constitution relevant to modern society?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
